section.div: Imagination should be the only limitation. If I reach this goal I'll be able to dedicate a large amount of time each week to continue to work on my projects. It will help me to continue to create learning content in the future!

div.p: Hi, I'm Michael! I'm a software engineer who is passionate about making open-source more accessible and building communities, online & offline. I'm a husband and father who enjoys spending time with my family. Some of my hobbies include 3D printing, paintball, gaming, and of course writing code! I once heard a quote that I try to live by as my life mantra "be a blessing, not a burden" - this drives me to continue to learn and push new exciting boundaries as I challenge myself.
I am heavily involved in the Raspberry Pi communities and Co-Founder of the Raspbernetes project. I also am involved in multiple CNCF projects and an open-source contributor.
The Raspbernetes project started with a goal to automate the setup and management of a Kubernetes cluster on Raspberry Pis. It aims to be completely declarative and idempotent.
It demonstrates how to implement enterprise-grade security, observability, and overall cluster management in a learning environment.
Check out more about the project https://github.com/raspbernetes

By sponsoring, you'll help us in our mission to continue to create awesome content to help others in their learning journey. The project has costs and sponsoring It helps to scale the project and cover the costs that are out of pocket expenses. Building technology to make a difference in the world of open-source and your support keeps it going!
